snippet: Mr. Tchicai played in Europe and in New York, composed works for orchestras and taught at the University of California in Davis.
abstract: John Tchicai, soft-toned Danish saxophonist who was at the center of the free-jazz movement in the mid-1960s, dies at age 76.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Tchicai played in Europe and in New York, composed works for orchestras and taught at the University of California in Davis.

headline.seo: John Tchicai, Saxophone Player in Free Jazz Movement, Dies at 76
headline.main: John Tchicai, Saxophone Player in Free Jazz Movement, Dies at 76
